race.comment: Ciaron Maher brings FIRST THOUGHT (3) down from NSW, in what looks a nice piece of placement. Was in the money first up at Nowra then could only manage eighth last time out over 1850m at Newcastle, but in a $60k Super Maiden. Only beaten 3-3/4 lengths, will be better for it, the extra 100m here is perfect at this stage of the prep and draws ideally. ASHINA (10) was beaten at $1.55 at Kerang two back but was too bad to be true and ran an improved race last time. She's in this up to her ears if she repeats the runs either side of the Kerang disaster. LICENTIOUS (12) ran the best race of her career last start, which came at this venue, and being by So You Think you would imagine she'll relish the further step up in trip. Gate one is a bonus. CHICKY WA WA (11) has run the best races of her career at her past two, probably thanks to being up to a suitable trip, so while the draw presents some potential issues, she's going too well to dismiss.
